	"keywords": "Software Development, Programming, Game Development, Software Engineering, Technology",
	"description": "Preface\nI have made a lot of games. The end phase of game development is usually hard.\nThe dreaded crunch, the extra mile to fix bugs and add polish can be very\narduous for all involved.\n\nIf you are lucky the crunch is driven by passion and a desire to achieve a\ncollective vision. If you are unlucky it’s driven by over commitment and\nimpossible deadlines. (In reality luck has nothing to do with it but that is a\ndiscussion for another time.)\n\nThe language we developers use when talking about bugs",
